2. LOCK-FREE MESSAGE PASSING BETWEEN THREADS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Never use Mutex<T> on the hot trading path. A mutex contention = thread park
= kernel syscall = microseconds of delay.

Architecture: two dedicated threads, zero locks between them.
  Thread 1 (WebSocket Ingestion) → Ring Buffer → Thread 2 (Execution)

use crossbeam::queue::ArrayQueue;
use std::sync::Arc;

// Bounded, lock-free SPSC queue
let queue: Arc<ArrayQueue<OrderEvent>> = Arc::new(ArrayQueue::new(1024));

// Thread 1: WebSocket ingestion
let q_producer = Arc::clone(&queue);
tokio::spawn(async move {
    while let Some(msg) = ws_stream.next().await {
        let event = parse_fast(&msg);
        // push never blocks — if full, oldest data is dropped
        let _ = q_producer.push(event);
    }
});

// Thread 2: Execution engine
let q_consumer = Arc::clone(&queue);
tokio::spawn(async move {
    loop {
        while let Some(event) = q_consumer.pop() {
            process_event(event).await;
        }
        tokio::task::yield_now().await;  // yield briefly when queue empty
    }
});

